                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Crude, irregular.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red.</seg>
                        <date>18th century.</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Titles and numbers of the Pss.; title of the first
                           Canticle; elements of the punctuation signs and text dividers; Ethiopic
                           numerals or their elements.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>

                     <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d1">
                        <locus target="#54r">54r</locus>: elaborate ornamental band separates Text I
                        and Text II.</decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- The Pss. are divided into groups of ten separated with a line of alternating black and red dots. - Frequently two verses of the text are written in one line. - Part of the line is taken up or down in very many cases: fols. 1v, 2r, 2v, 3r, 3v, 4r, etc. - Omitted lines are added interlineally with out a tämälläs-sign: fols. 37r, 38v, 40r - Erasure marked with thin lines (?): fols. 13r, 24v</item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
                  <bindingDesc>
